# Worker rules

Single file: `workers/api-proxy.js` (~5400 lines). Dispatch is a long `if/else` chain near the bottom of the file. **There is no framework** (no Hono, no itty-router) — raw `fetch` event handlers.

## Routes (exactly 31 — do not invent)

### AI
- `POST /v1/chat` — Anthropic proxy. Plan-gated, KV rate-limited per user per day. Body: `{messages, system, catalog}`. Response: `{text, usage: {queries_today, queries_limit}}`.

### Stripe (6)
- `POST /stripe/webhook` — handles `checkout.session.completed`, `customer.subscription.updated`, `customer.subscription.deleted`, `invoice.payment_succeeded`
- `GET /stripe/subscription`
- `POST /stripe/subscription/schedule-downgrade`
- `POST /stripe/create-customer`
- `POST /stripe/create-subscription`
- `POST /stripe/create-portal-session`

### Account billing (2)
- `POST /api/cancel-subscription` — Bearer; schedule cancel at period end; optional Resend email
- `POST /api/reactivate-subscription` — Bearer; clear scheduled cancel

### Auth-adjacent (4)
- `POST /auth/signup` — Turnstile + IP RL → Supabase signup (anon key)
- `POST /auth/password-reset` — Turnstile + IP RL → Supabase recover (anon key)
- `POST /turnstile/verify`
- `POST /account/delete` — service-role cascading delete

### Member profiles (7)
- `GET /member-profiles` — list caller's profiles
- `POST /member-profiles` — create (plan slot limit)
- `PATCH /member-profiles/{id}` — update many fields
- `DELETE /member-profiles/{id}` — non-default only
- `GET /member-profiles/handle-available?handle=`
- `GET /member-profiles/public?handle=` — **no auth**
- `GET /member-profiles/search?q=`

### Social (3)
- `POST /member-follows`
- `DELETE /member-follows`
- `GET /member-follows/following?profile_id=`

### R2 images (5)
- `POST /stack-photo` — multipart upload to `stack-photos` R2 bucket
- `POST /upload-stack-photo` — alias
- `GET /stack-photo?key=…` — authenticated private read (caller's prefix only)
- `GET /avatars/{key}` — **public** read, no auth, no rate limit. Never rate-limit these.
- `POST /avatars` / `PUT /avatars`

## Model routing

```js
const MODEL_ENTRY_PRO  = "claude-haiku-4-5-20251001";
const MODEL_ELITE_GOAT = "claude-sonnet-4-6";
```

`modelForPlan(plan)` returns one. **Plan is read from `public.profiles.plan` via service role — never from the client payload.**

## max_tokens caps

| Plan | Cap |
|---|---|
| Entry / Pro | 1024 |
| Elite | 2048 |
| GOAT | 4096 |

`maxTokensCapForPlan(plan, env)` is the source of truth.

## Daily query limits

| Plan | Limit |
|---|---|
| Entry | 2 |
| Pro | 4 |
| Elite | 8 |
| GOAT | 16 |

Counter in KV at `rl:{userId}:{YYYY-MM-DD}` with 90,000s TTL.

- `readDailyQueryRateLimit` **before** the Anthropic call (to check)
- `incrementDailyQueryRateLimit` **after** a successful response (don't charge failed calls)

## IP rate limits

`checkIpRateLimit(env, ip, type)` — types: `r2_write`, `r2_read`, `auth`, `api`. Public avatar reads (`GET/HEAD/OPTIONS /avatars/{key}`) bypass entirely. **Fails-closed in production if KV is missing.**

